  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Copper Shortsword</b> is an early-game metal <linked>shortsword</linked>. Its alternate ore counterpart is the <linked>Tin Shortsword</linked>.",
    "On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console</linked>, <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console</linked>, and <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile</linked> versions, all newly created non-<span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Journey Mode</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span> characters will spawn with a Copper Shortsword in their first <linked>inventory</linked> slot, and it is possible that it can have a <linked>modifier</linked> already applied to it. On the <linked>3DS</linked><linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked> versions, newly created players will spawn with a <linked>Wooden Sword</linked> instead of a Copper Shortsword. In <span class=\"eil\"><span>Journey Mode</span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span>, newly created characters will spawn with an <linked>Iron Shortsword</linked> instead of a Copper Shortsword.",
    "Like all shortswords, the Copper Shortsword has a very limited range and attacks with a stabbing motion <span class=\"etxt\"><span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span><span>at any direction</span></span> / <span class=\"etxt\"><span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Old-gen console and 3DS versions)</span></span><span>horizontally in front of the player</span></span>, instead of an arc. This makes it almost useless against flying or jumping enemies, although its high attack rate makes it somewhat effective against weaker <linked>fighter</linked> type enemies.",
    "Its best <linked>modifier</linked> is <b>Legendary</b>."
  ],
